Source: qos
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/appstonia/pg_qos

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-qos
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-qos
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: QoS resource governor extension for PostgreSQL
  QoS is a PostgreSQL extension that provides resource governance for sessions and queries.
  It can cap CPU usage, work_mem, and concurrent transaction/statement limits per role and database.
  This package contains the qos extension build for PostgreSQL PGVERSION.
